| Product Extraction – Schema & Category Field Rules |

| Overview |
This document defines the rules governing the JSON output returned by the AI extraction model for the Seller Admin Panel – Product Box Image Extraction feature.

| File |
product_schema.json --- JSON Schema (draft-07) for validation
categories.json --- Category list in array format for prompting

| Field Rules |
(1) name — string | null

-Extract the main product title exactly as printed on the packaging.
-Do not paraphrase or translate.
-Max length: 255 characters.
-Set to null if not visible on packaging.

(2) brand — string | null

-Extract the brand name as printed. Do not guess or infer.
-Max length: 255 characters.
-Set to null if not visible.

(3) category — string | null

-Must be an exact match from categories.json.
-Never return a value outside the allowed list.

(4) description — string | null

-Summarize visible product specifications.
-Based only on what is visible on the packaging — do not add external knowledge.
-Max length: 1000 characters.
-Set to null if insufficient packaging information exists.

(5) manufacturing_country — string | null

-Max length: 100 characters.
-Set to null if not found on packaging.

(6) estimated_wholesale_price_azn — float | null 

-Represents the estimated wholesale price in AZN.
-Must be a positive number. Set to null if estimation is not possible.

(7) estimated_retail_price_azn — float | null

-Represents the estimated retail price in AZN.
-Typically computed as: retail = wholesale × markup.
-Must be a positive number. Set to null if wholesale is also null.

(8) confidence_score — float (always required, never null)

-Reflects the overall extraction confidence for the entire response.
-Range: 0.0 to 1.0.
-Always present. This is the only field that cannot be null.
-Computed from:
    --Number of non-null fields extracted
    --Category match success
    --Presence of manufacturing country
    --Price estimation source (internal vs. model)

| Strict Rules for All Fields |
-1- Never hallucinate. If information is not visible on the packaging, return null
-2- Category must match the allowed list. Unknown categories are rejected by the validation layer and set to null.
-3- Prices must be positive floats. Negative or zero prices fail validation and are set to null.